dismissalText.commentary: Imrul Kayes st Chakabva b Sikandar Raza 73 (95b 6x4 4x6 116m) SR: 76.84

dismissalComment.html: Raza halts the surging opening stand. Kayes jumps out of the crease, the bowler loops it up and finds some turn as well. Kayes has a big whoosh at it, and misses. Chakabva does the rest, though on the second attempt

dismissalText.commentary: Tamim Iqbal st Chakabva b Cremer 73 (98b 7x4 1x6 138m) SR: 74.48

dismissalComment.html: No century for Tamim either. Cremer generates extra bounce again, Tamim aims to cut. He can only chop it over the top of the stumps. The keeper grabs the ball on the first bounce and takes the bails off. Given out as stumped, though. Tamim can't ground his bat in time

dismissalText.commentary: Mustafizur Rahman run out (Sikandar Raza/Chakabva) 1 (1b 0x4 0x6 1m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: Another run out, to finish off the innings. Hurled full on off, Mustafiz goes low for the slog sweep. He checks his shot and drags it to long-on. He hustles for the second but is run out at the keeper's end

dismissalText.long: c Sabbir Rahman b Mashrafe Mortaza
dismissalText.commentary: Sean Williams c Sabbir Rahman b Mashrafe Mortaza 64 (84b 5x4 0x6 130m) SR: 76.19

dismissalComment.html: Mashrafe takes down Williams. He aims to step out, the Bangladesh captain bangs it short. He miscues it and Sabbir settles under the skier at short cover

dismissalText.commentary: Elton Chigumbura b Sabbir Rahman 45 (47b 6x4 0x6 57m) SR: 95.74

dismissalComment.html: bowled'em. Pushed much quicker through the air, Chigumbura, who hangs back, can't connect with his leg-side whip. The ball scoots low and thuds into middle. Sabbir looks pleased and that's a big wicket for the hosts

headshotImage.caption: Mustafizur Rahman player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: bang, Mustafiz tilts the middle stump back as Mirpur roars. Pretty full and nips back in a bit to rip through the gate. Top, top ball, this, to follow the warm-up ball

image.caption: Regis Chakabva
image.longCaption: Regis Chakabva portrait, World Cup 2011, February 11, 2011

dismissalComment.html: Mustafiz strikes, again! Looks like a slower cutter, Chakabva aims to loft drive. But is tricked by the lack of pace, and spoons the ball into the lap of Nasir at cover.. End of a scratchy innings

Sabbir plucks out a stunner after missing one earlier. He lands on his elbow again, but hangs on. Raza is sent packing. Nice and full on middle, Raza seeks to flick but loops it to the off side off a leading edge. Sabbir runs to his left from mid-on, dives full stretch to his left, snapping it up near the mid-off region. He takes his cap off and celebrates!

dismissalText.commentary: Taurai Muzarabani c & b Arafat Sunny 0 (5b 0x4 0x6 6m) SR: 0

commentTextItems.html: That is that! Bangladesh sweep the series 3-0, they win the final ODI by 61 runs. Loopier and drifts in, another soft dismissal, sums up the story for Zimbabwe. Feebly chipped back to the bowler

commentPostTextItems.html: 9pm: Mashrafe collects the trophy and is joined by his team-mates. Zimbabwe have been killed off again. And a toy tiger joins the celebrations as well. Many thanks for your company and comments. Kept me on my toes. Do watch out for analyses from Mohammad Isam. Be back for the T20 series. Until then, goodbye and good night!

Chigumbura: It is disappointing once again. We thought they may score 300-plus score but we kept them to about 270 and managed to pull it back. But again we lost wickets and that's always difficult. T20 is a different version and we have to play different cricket.

Tamim is the Man of the Match. Here he is again: I think I was batting well from the first game. I din't get the big score. We started well with me and Imrul and Mustafiz finished it. There is always room for improvement. We have won the series, so no complaints.

Mushfiqur, Man of the Series: We have really worked hard and it has paid off. The bowlers did their job and the top order did well. It is not an easy wicket to chase. Mustafiz and Al-Amin had lots of overs in the end. It is really pleasing for our team.
Mashrafe: We don't have Shakib, so we have to keep changing bowlers. The dressing room is relaxed. Thanks to the supporters for coming and helping us.

8:40pm : Mashrafe leads his team off the field. Another dominant display from Bangladesh. Mustafiz struck with his second ball to ride his car through Chamu's gate, and also dismissed the other opener - Chakabva. Zimbabwe, however, recovered through Williams and Chigumbura who added 80 together. Williams, benefiting from a couple of reprieves, went on to score the first fifty by a Zimbabwe player this series, but Mustafiz (off)cut his way through the lower order to claim his third five-wicket haul in his ninth ODI.

Tamim: "We have been playing well for the last one year. Hats off to Mustafiz again. Everybody chipped in. When you win games you get confidence. We had planed well and execute it well. The ODIs are over and T20 is a different ball game. With the T20 World Cup coming up, the two T20s are important for us. BPL is happening and that is important for us."
Mohammad Islam: "Mash for Man of the Tournament...Mash for President....Mash for Prime Minister!"
preetom: "expected mustafiz to be the man of the match"
Aftiar: "Interesting stat: No Bangladeshi batsmen got out by LBW in this series!"

dismissalText.long: c Nasir Hossain b Mustafizur Rahman
dismissalText.commentary: Regis Chakabva c Nasir Hossain b Mustafizur Rahman 17 (20b 2x4 0x6 33m) SR: 85

dismissalComment.html: Mustafiz strikes, again! Looks like a slower cutter, Chakabva aims to loft drive. But is tricked by the lack of pace, and spoons the ball into the lap of Nasir at cover.. End of a scratchy innings

dismissalText.commentary: Craig Ervine lbw b Nasir Hossain 21 (25b 4x4 0x6 42m) SR: 84

dismissalComment.html: Ervine plays back and is trapped plumb in front. He should have been forward to that. Slides on quick and undoes Ervine, pinging him on the back pad. Mustafiz was setting up to bowl this over but Mashrafe and Tamim called in Nasir, who delivered

dismissalText.long: c Sabbir Rahman b Mashrafe Mortaza
dismissalText.commentary: Sean Williams c Sabbir Rahman b Mashrafe Mortaza 64 (84b 5x4 0x6 130m) SR: 76.19

dismissalComment.html: Mashrafe takes down Williams. He aims to step out, the Bangladesh captain bangs it short. He miscues it and Sabbir settles under the skier at short cover

dismissalText.commentary: Elton Chigumbura b Sabbir Rahman 45 (47b 6x4 0x6 57m) SR: 95.74

dismissalComment.html: bowled'em. Pushed much quicker through the air, Chigumbura, who hangs back, can't connect with his leg-side whip. The ball scoots low and thuds into middle. Sabbir looks pleased and that's a big wicket for the hosts

dismissalText.long: c Nasir Hossain b Al-Amin Hossain
dismissalText.commentary: Malcolm Waller c Nasir Hossain b Al-Amin Hossain 32 (40b 4x4 0x6 54m) SR: 80

dismissalComment.html: fine, leaping catch from Nasir. The returning Al-Amin provides the breakthrough. Good length and no movement outside off, Waller has a crack at it and loft-drives it... Nasir propels himself upward and snaffles it at cover

dismissalText.long: c Sabbir Rahman b Mustafizur Rahman
dismissalText.commentary: Sikandar Raza c Sabbir Rahman b Mustafizur Rahman 9 (12b 1x4 0x6 23m) SR: 75

dismissalComment.html: Sabbir plucks out a stunner after missing one earlier. He lands on his elbow again, but hangs on. Raza is sent packing. Nice and full on middle, Raza seeks to flick but loops it to the off side off a leading edge. Sabbir runs to his left from mid-on, dives full stretch to his left, snapping it up near the mid-off region. He takes his cap off and celebrates!

dismissalComment.html: That is that! Bangladesh sweep the series 3-0, they win the final ODI by 61 runs. Loopier and drifts in, another soft dismissal, sums up the story for Zimbabwe. Feebly chipped back to the bowler

recentReportStory.title: Mustafizur five-for seals Bangladesh's 3-0 sweep
recentReportStory.subTitle: Bangladesh v Zimbabwe, 3rd ODI, Mirpur
recentReportStory.summary: Tamim Iqbal and Imrul Kayes set the platform by stroking 73 each, before Mahmudullah's late fireworks helped Bangladesh ride a middle-order wobble to post 276/9 in the third ODI against Zimbabwe in Mirpur
recentReportStory.byline: The Report by Mohammad Isam in Mirpur

recentPreviewStory.title: Bangladesh seek another clean sweep
recentPreviewStory.subTitle: Bangladesh v Zimbabwe, 3rd ODI, Mirpur
recentPreviewStory.summary: Bangladesh have plenty to be cheerful for this year, beating Pakistan, India and South Africa in a remarkable period in the country's cricketing history; they'll want to add to that list
